item.description:
@function if($condition, $if-true, $if-false) Parameters condition
A truthy or falsey value. if-true
The value returned if the $condition parameter evaulates to true. if-false
The value returned if the $condition parameter evaulates to false. Returns Either the second parameter if the first parameter evaluates to a truthy value, or the third parameter otherwise.
Examples @debug if(true, 1px, 2px); // 1px; @debug if(false, 1px, 2px); // 2px;

@function tan($angle) Parameters angle
An angle, or any number. If the input has no unit, then it&rsquo;s treated as radians. Returns The tangent of the angle angle.
If the angle is infinity or -infinity, NaN is returned. If the angle is -0, -0 is returned.
